# Signal Bundle from Minder — Session 56

## What Changed

### 1. WAI-Lugs.jsonl is archive-only — bytype/signal/undelivered/ is canonical (impact 9)

WAI-Lugs.jsonl was being used as the active signal store, but it is not. It is the archive index for completed/retired lugs. Active signals must be written to `WAI-Spoke/lugs/bytype/signal/undelivered/{id}.json`.

**Migration path:** WAI-Signals.jsonl (retired) → WAI-Lugs.jsonl (transitional, now archive-only) → bytype/signal/undelivered/ (canonical).

Signals in WAI-Lugs.jsonl are unreachable by the routing gate and Gardener Tender. 23 open signal lugs were found in WAI-Lugs.jsonl that needed migration to bytype/.

## Why It Matters

Any spoke still appending signals to WAI-Lugs.jsonl has invisible signals — the routing gate, hub bulletin (Step 9c), and Tender all operate on the file-based store. The fix is additive (write to bytype/) and non-destructive (WAI-Lugs.jsonl remains as archive).

## Migration Instructions

1. For each active signal in WAI-Lugs.jsonl (`s: "o"` or `status: "undelivered"`): write as `{id}.json` to `WAI-Spoke/lugs/bytype/signal/undelivered/`
2. Leave WAI-Lugs.jsonl untouched (archive)
3. Update any protocol steps that say "append signal to WAI-Lugs.jsonl" to write to `bytype/signal/undelivered/` instead

## Prerequisites

None — additive change.

